    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1954-12-21T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-01-22T20:00:00-05:00" n="131" subtype="editorial-note"
                type="document" xml:id="d131">
                <head>No. 131<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Editorial Note</hi>
                </head>
                <p>Following their conversation on November 8 (see <ref target="#d126">Document
                        126</ref>), <persName corresp="#p_MG1">McGhee</persName> and <persName
                        corresp="#p_MM1">Mosadeq</persName> talked further on November 13 and twice
                    on both November 15 and 17. During these conversations <persName
                        corresp="#p_MG1">McGhee</persName> proposed various solutions to the oil
                    question, including the possibility of an Anglo-Dutch-American consortium and a
                    World Bank trusteeship of the Abadan refinery, but none of the plans was
                    satisfactory to <persName corresp="#p_MM1">Mosadeq</persName>. The Iranian Prime
                    Minister insisted on a Persian Gulf price of $1.75 per barrel, while <persName
                        corresp="#p_MG1">McGhee</persName> repeated that such insistence precluded
                    any settlement.</p>
                <p>At their second meeting on November 15 <persName corresp="#p_MG1"
                        >McGhee</persName> also delivered President <persName corresp="#p_THS1"
                        >Truman</persName>’s interim reply to <persName corresp="#p_MM1"
                        >Mosadeq</persName>’s request (see <ref target="#d126fn4">footnote 4,
                        Document 126</ref>) for economic assistance, which stated that the request
                    was being considered and a further reply would be forthcoming.</p>
                <p>Memoranda of the five conversations between <persName corresp="#p_MG1"
                        >McGhee</persName> and <persName corresp="#p_MM1">Mosadeq</persName> are in
                    file 888.2553/8–1051. No copy of President <persName corresp="#p_THS1"
                        >Truman</persName>’s interim reply has been found in Department of State
                    files, but it is <pb facs="0310" n="284" xml:id="pg_284"/> described in the
                    memoranda of conversation for November 15 and 17, referred to above.</p>
            </div>
